  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points. The review panel concluded that the overall body of evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level: seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed, validation data from the FDA benchmark dataset provide geometric and flow-regime relevance, and the numerical verification activities meet internal quality gates. A residual gap in model-form fidelity was noted but judged acceptable given the conservative hemolysis threshold applied. Decision: Accepted.",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-index",
