      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version-controlled release with documented unit and regression test suite passing rate ≥ 95%.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 used under FDA-recognized software quality plan. Regression suite pass rate 98.3%. Version control and change-management records complete. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate convergence to analytical or manufactured solutions for laminar and turbulent channel flows at order consistent with discretization scheme.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to laminar Poiseuille flow and Womersley oscillatory flow. Observed order of accuracy 1.92 (second-order scheme). Turbulent benchmark (periodic hill) residuals within published reference data band. Code verification complete at required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) on hemolysis-relevant shear stress must be ≤ 5% on the fine mesh; Richardson extrapolation must confirm monotonic convergence across three mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels evaluated: 2.1 M, 6.8 M, and 18.4 M cells. GCI on volume-averaged scalar shear stress is 14.3% between medium and fine meshes — above the 5% threshold. Oscillatory convergence observed in the impeller tip-clearance region; Richardson extrapolation could not be applied there. Resource constraints precluded a fourth refinement level. Achieved level 2 against required level 4. The panel noted this gap but characterised it as bounded by the conservative hemolysis threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, temperature) must be reproduced in simulation within ±2% of nominal values.",
      "rationale": "All five flow-speed operating points replicated within ±1.1% of experimental set-points. Blood analogue viscosity matched to 0.8% at 37 °C. Test conditions factor fully satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH must agree with measured NIH within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bands at ≥ 80% of operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions fall within combined uncertainty bands at 4 of 5 operating points (80%). At the fifth point (6 L/min, 4500 RPM) the prediction exceeds measured NIH by 22% — a conservative over-prediction. Output comparison factor satisfied at required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs (NIH, scalar shear stress distribution) must be directly traceable to the regulatory submission QoIs.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary regulatory QoI. Scalar shear stress distribution is the intermediate QoI feeding the hemolysis power-law model. Full traceability documented in the V&V plan. Relevance of QoIs confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry and blood analogue as the COU; operating envelope must overlap with VAD clinical operating range.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used in both validation and COU simulation. Blood analogue (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) consistent with ASTM F1841. Operating envelope (3–6 L/min, 2500–4500 RPM) spans the clinical VAD range. Validation activity relevance confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Round-off and iterative convergence errors must be quantified and shown negligible relative to discretization error; floating-point arithmetic sensitivity study required.",
      "rationale": "Solver error quantification was scoped as an epistemic gap at MRL 5. Iterative residuals were monitored (all below 1×10⁻⁵) but no formal floating-point sensitivity or round-off analysis was performed. Factor not assessed; achieved level assigned 1 by default against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup must be independently reviewed by a second analyst; checklist-based review covering boundary conditions, material properties, and solver settings required.",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst review was planned but not completed within the submission timeline. Use error factor flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection must be justified by sensitivity study comparing at least two RANS closures and one scale-resolving approach; hemolysis power-law constant must be calibrated to device-specific data.",
      "rationale": "Two RANS closures compared (SST k-ω and realizable k-ε); NIH predictions differ by up to 31% between models in the tip-clearance region. Scale-resolving (LES) simulation was not performed. Hemolysis power-law constants (C, α, β) taken from Giersiepen et al. without device-specific recalibration. Model form uncertainty is the dominant source of prediction uncertainty per the Monte Carlo analysis. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (inlet velocity profile, fluid rheology parameters, wall roughness) must be characterised with probability distributions and propagated via Monte Carlo; sensitivity indices (Sobol) required.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo propagation was performed on inlet boundary conditions only. Fluid rheology and wall roughness were treated as deterministic. Sobol sensitivity indices were not computed. Model inputs factor assessed as not-assessed for the full required scope; achieved level 1 against required level 4."
